Rating: 4
This is indeed the best chocolate cake around. Years ago, I baked professionally, which has made me pretty picky, but I made this recipe for about 18 people last weekend and everyone agreed it was the best. A few notes: 1) It should be made in three 9 inch cake pans, NOT 8 inch. The batter fit perfectly with that change. 2)The better the chocolate, the better the cake. 3) When the cake is cool, cut the tops off to level the cake and you'll have a beautiful but enormous cake. You'll get a good 20 slices out of this cake, more than the recipe suggests. 4) Finally, I found that, with the 9" cake pans, the amount of frosting was light, so I filled the 2 middle layers with freshly whipped cream and just put a thick layer of the icing on the top and sides. I served it with a dollop of fresh whipped cream and a cold glass of Guinness. Cheers!

