I am passing along reviews from the people who ate this after I made it. Several people told me they don't usually like cake but they were mad for it. The entire thing was gone in about 15 minutes. I did make some minor changes-- I followed the tips about baking at 325. I also added about 1/4 c. of stout to the ganache. Quality ingredients make all the difference, especially in the ganache. I used Ghirardelli chocolate and sweetened it with about 1/3 c. of sugar because my friend whose birthday I baked this for likes sweeter chocolate. I didn't have much time to cool the ganache so, after about 10 minutes in the refrigerator, I put it in the freezer and mixed it every five minutes for about 25-30 minutes total. It turned out perfect. My friend was over the moon and said it was the best cake she's ever had. Many asked for the recipe and another friend asked that I make this for her upcoming birthday. This will definitely be my go-to cake.

