just made for second time and got the frosting perfect this time!! One must be sure to not allow the whipping cream to go beyond the point of simmer....if you do, then it won't thicken as that happened the 1st time. This time, I was diligent and the frosting was exactly the same consistency as at the Brewery when I had the fatal slice of cake that has hooked me forever....I will bake my OWN birthday cake from now on...this will replace a choc mousse "bomb" cake that I thought was the best..... I baked this Stout cake for my friend's birthday last nite and her family went absolutely wild for it....who wouldn't!? ENJOY! And SO easy to make!

