I needed to make a cake for an event and boy am I glad I chose this one!!! I'll be brief since there are so many other great reviews on here: 1. I used Samuel Smith's Oatmeal Stout as someone recommended and it worked great; 2. I used 39" cake pans and still had enough extra batter to make 2 small samples in ramekins for testing (so yes, LOTS of batter...be sure your mixing bowl is HUGE); 3. There was not nearly enough frosting. I ended up making 1.5x the amount of frosting and probably should have just doubled it; 4. The cake is MUCH better on day 2, so make it ahead. I put it in the fridge overnight and then let it sit out all day on the 2nd day to come to room temp. The frosting held and the cake is much better at room temp; 5. I wanted to fancy it up a bit and covered the top with semi-sweet and white chocolate curls. This cake is delicious and an absolute show stopper, so do yourself a favor and make it!

