Rating: 4
Absolutely wonderful cake! I have made it dozens of times with different stouts, and all turned out delicious. However, I think there is a clear stout winner: Samuel Smith's Oatmeal Stout. It's my favorite stout and works beautifully with the rest of the flavors. I'm sticking with it. I live at high elevation and never tinkered with the recipe even though it rose too fast and was on the dry side. I did adjust my most recent batch, and it turned out fantastic and moist. I will be keeping the alterations. Altitude adjustments for 5280 ft: Preheat oven to 370 degrees, Add an additional 2T of stout, Subtract 2T butter, Subtract 4T sugar, Subtract 3/8t baking soda, Add an additional egg, Add an additional 1T sour cream. Bake for 30 minutes. Sometimes I find the delicious frosting to be a little on the runny side, even when chilled for over 2 hours. I think I will be adding more chocolate to see if it sets a little better.

