Rating: 4
Okay, so I made cupcakes out of this recipe, not changing anything except to substitute 1/2 of the sour cream for low fat vanilla yogurt (I ran out of sour cream). The day that I made them, I have to say that I was not all that impressed. They seemed overwhelmingly 'stouty' to me, and the chocolate flavor was barely a whisper. However, after filling them with a Kahlua cream filling and refrigerating them overnight, these cupcakes turned into the most gloriously rich and dense cupcakes I have ever made. The stout flavor had sort of taken a back seat (but definitely did not disappear) to the rich chocolate flavor at this point. Oh my god, the cake is actually addictive. Such an interesting taste combination. I have not figured out what frosting to use for these little bundles of yummyness, but I am thinking something with liquer in it. Maybe Irish Cream frosting of some kind. This recipe is definitely a keeper; I think it will be my go- to cake recipe for St. Patricks's Day from now on. NOTE: definitely use UNSALTED butter, otherwise these will be too salty. The beer is already salty, plus with the additional salt added into the recipe you really don't want any more salt in the form of butter. I made the mistake of using salted butter, and I ended up adding about 1/2 cup more sugar to the batter to compensate for the saltiness.

