Rating: 4
I made this recipe with no adjustments to ingredients. I wanted it for work and Christmas gifts so I did not make a full-sized cake. The recipe made 96 mini-cupcakes as well as two 6"x2" round cakes. At the suggestion of another reviewer, I poured the batter into a big Ziplock bag, and cut a tiny corner off, and used it like a large "pastry bag" to fill the paper-lined pans....worked like a charm! I used very high quality cocoa and chocolate; I learned a long time ago it makes a huge difference. The icing is very much like ganache (yum). I let it cool just a bit before dipping the cupcakes in it; it made a wonderfully easy glaze. By the time I was finished dipping 96 cupcakes, it was the perfect consistency to beautifully ice the two little cakes. Overall, VERY impressive and received rave reviews from LOTS of co-workers and friends. This is a keeper!

