Rating: 3
I would give this 3.5 forks if I could. Really really good! For those who are wondering, as I was, there isn't a stout flavor in the finished case (I used Young's chocolate stout). There's an underlying note that your foodie/chocoholic friends might notice, but it certainly nothing that most people will pick up on - they'll just think it tastes great! I made 2/3 of a recipe (only had 1 cup sour cream), and used 2 cups AP flour with 1 cup cake flour, and the texture - while dense - was good. (btw, this made one 2" high 8" round and 20 regular cupcakes). Cut sugar to 2.5 cups. Final note - didn't use the icing from the recipe. Used the Foolproof Chocolate Frosting recipe from America's Test Kitchen. It was a great combination. Get that recipe while you can.

