Halved recipe, First baked 4 dozen mini cupcakes (used paper liners), left extra batter out on counter. Then removed mini-cupcakes from pans... cleaned, cooled & relined them with papers and took remaining batter and I was able to make an additional 2 dozen mini cupcakes. They looked the same as the first ones. Oven set as recipe suggested, 350 degrees. I baked both times 15-16 minutes & they tested done with a toothpick. A note, I only filled the cupcakes 2/3+ full & they baked mostly flat a little above the liner, no drips or runny mess. The batter is extremely runny so I put it into a gallon size zip lock bag, cut the corner & used this to fill the cupcake tins.

