Rating: 4
I LOVE LOVE LOVE this cake! I have made it several times over the years and it never disappoints. I read a couple of the reviews posted that complained about the frosting. It IS NOT thick enough when you first make it, because it is still HOT. That does make a nice icing if you want to drizzle it on. But if you want traditional frosting, follow the directions, refridgerate (and stir) the frosting and have patience. The frosting comes out better than store bought for sure. Two notes: 1. I like to add sliced strawberries to the center ( I only make this a double layer cake) The berries break up the chocolate for a fresh little surprise. 2. I keep a container with a mixture of whole wheat and unbleached AP flours with a little wheat germ thrown into the mix for all of my baking. I recently made this cake with that. No one seemed to notice the difference, and I feel good knowing there is a little "healthiness" in this truly decadent cake.

