Rating: 4
I made these cakes last night so they could sit for 3 days (before Valentine's Day) - despite reading all the reviews, I forgot that they would rise! I made a 1/2 batch and poured it in three little heart springform pans, and the cakes rose up almost 1.5 inches above the top of the pans - they look beautiful, (almost like monkeybread) although they lost their heart shape. I used the butter wrapper to grease the pans, as well as canola oil spray just in case, and they slipped right out of the springform crystal-clean, so there's not really a need for parchment paper. I cut the 3 puffy hearts in half, spread a thick layer of ganache, and then still had plenty for the sides and top, even with a 1/2 batch. I used a little more stout (double chocolate) just for fun, and splenda instead of sugar (so I'd feel a little less guilty), and I'm happy the ganache is so sweet (semi-sweet ghiradelli chocolate). I can't wait to try these in 3 days!

