This is an incredibly chocolate cake that isn't too sweet. In addition to frosting the cake with the chocolate icing, I add raspberry preserves between the layers along with the chocolate icing. Once the cake is frosted, I decorate it with large chocolate rosettes around the base of the cake. (I use a pastry bag with a large rosette tip.) Then I insert a fresh raspberry into the center of each rosette. I also drizzle dark chocolate on the top of the cake to complete the presentation. The last time I made this cake, I only had 3 matching pans with 1.5 inch sides, so I made cup cakes with the balance of batter. I decorated the top of each cupcake with a chocolate rosette and a raspberry. The kids loved them!

