Rating: 4
Astonishing! Very easy to make, amazing taste, perfect moisture, excellent crumb. 10 forks! I suspect the variety of experiences reflects the quality of the ingredients used. I used Callebaut cocoa powder and Young's Double Chocolate Stout (the large cans provide 2 cups). Results may also vary given the flour used. I have used Pillsbury unbleached...will try bleached to see if texture becomes a bit firmer...unbleached results in a very tender cake, too tender, for example, for use as german chocolate cake base, but perfect for buttercream, whipped cream or ganache. I also use cocoa powder instead of flour to prep pans, which are straight-edged Chicago Metal pans (baked with parchment circles and cake strips). Comes out flawlessly after 10 minutes. Should be made the day before eating for best taste...no stout or yeast taste at all, just deep chocolate tones. Freezes beautifully. Halve the recipe for 2 or 3 8-inch pans or 1 or 2 9-inch. Full recipe requires 3 9-inch pans or 4 8-inch. This is the best chocolate cake recipe I have ever come across...for ease of making, simplicity of ingredients and overall taste, moisture and texture. And for adaptability...layer cake, bundt cake, cupcakes....all work extremely well. A must-have recipe.

