Rating: 4
Excellent! Bake it the day before you plan to serve it and you will be thrilled with the full chocolate flavor and tender texture. I baked a 3/4 batch in my 12 cup Nordic Bundt (exactly 60 minutes) and had enough batter left over for two cupcakes. I used the frosting as a glaze while the cake was still warm and covered it immediately with the hot icing mixture. Do this by putting a sheet of parchment under the cooling rack to catch the excess and tap the rack (and cake) on the counter to encourage the icing to run down the sides. If you miss spots, you can scrape up the puddle under the cake cooling rack and pour it over again. Tap the cake rack firmly on the counter and the icing will run down. The result is a shiny, glazed show stopper! My only regret was using top-quality 70% chocolate for the glaze. The chocolate amateurs and children thought the frosting was too rich. I recommend Toll House morsels or no more than 55% chocolate. The flavor of the cake is so intense you almost don't need frosting.

