Rating: 4
I love this cake. so much. I like it just the way it is. I commented earlier about not wanting to add beer to the recipe because my room mate can't have alcohol for religious reasons (yes, I know it cooks off, but that's not the point). In any event, I've found a great way to substitute out the stout (although its really good with the stout). Use a good "near-beer" like Claustahler, something flavorful. Use it for all the stout called for, but minus 2 Tablespoons. Add 2 Tablespoons black strap molasses. This replicates the rich sweetness of stout!

