Rating: 4
SO GOOD!!!! i used murphy's stout and trader joe's cocoa and chocolate. i halved it, i think it would still feed twelve, easy. i also used full fat greek yogurt instead of sour cream, cause i didn't realize about the sour cream until after i was home from the store. about the ganache, don't chill it. just let the cake cool completely, then pour the ganache over. kind of spread it around with a spatula. it's MUCH easier this way, and will look all shiny and stuff. the less you mess with it, the shinier it will be. also, bakery trick- rip off four strips of parchment or wax paper and place the cake on top on them. pour the ganache over and then at the end, you can just pull away the parchment strips and voila! no mess.

