Rating: 0
I would like to try this recipe, and yet at this time I would like to help out the cook who couldn't serve the cake to the friend because of the alcohol. The alcohol evaporates when being combined and then heated for 35 minutes in such a hot oven, which makes it no longer alcoholic, so perhaps that could ease your mind about the recipe. It would be alcoholic if the Guiness were poured over the cake after baking. Almost every dessert has an alcoholic flavouring in the recipe (vanilla, almond extract, lemon extract, etc.). Some cookie recipes use as much as 1 tablespoon of vanilla plus another extract. I do not drink alcoholic beverages for religious reasons either. I hope this helps out.

Rating: 4
In reply to previous message about cooking the cake without alcohol...when you heat (i.e. bake or cook) anything with beer, liquor, etc. the alcohol evaporates off. You don't have to change the recipie for non-alcohol friends because beer adds ONLY great flavor, not the intoxicating effects.

