As a chocoholic myself I concur that this recipe is fabulous- not too sweet and very moist. In fact, the moistness was the only thing that gave me a problem as the layers wanted to stick to the cooling racks. I used 9 inch pans (no 8-inch ones to be found here in the boonies) which still took about the same amount of time to bake. Rave reviews from family and co-workers; I'll definitely make this again and again. It was also interesting to learn that half a chocolate cake layer will not even phase a larcenous cattle dog (no matter what veterinary advice we've heard to the contrary!)

