I made this cake yesterday for an Irish party. I had a time constraint, so I used aluminum throw away cake pans. Big mistake! The cakes need the full two inches of side height. The cake overflowed onto my oven and smelled downright nasty as the batter burned. But, after all was said and done, the cake was outstanding. Didn't have time for cooling and setting to construct the layers, so I put each cake on a plate and poured the semi-cooled ganache over the cakes and presented our friends with a single layer of the most sinful chocolate cake ever. Had I layered it, the cake would have been about 7 inches tall! I may try to make it in layers with 9" pans for thinner layers. This is one rich cake.

