Thanks to many reviewers for this recipe. I went ahead and tried to make this cake last weekend, for my boyfriend's birthday. I should have, though, tested the recipe out before doing it on the same day I invited friends over. The cake is good, but I'm not falling in love with it. I halved the recipe (recommended by reviewers) and baked it in the "bundt" mold. The batter was not enough for the "bundt" mold though. I found that the baking time is a bit off as well. I think if I'll try it again, I'll do it in an hour ( I took the cake out at the recommended time by the recipe, and the middle of the bundt cake is still undone) The amount of chocolate in this recipe isn't enough, I think. I used 1 cup cocoa powder instead. All in all, it's a good and easy cake to do, but it's not "a dish beyond compare."

