Rating: 4
This is a great chocolate cake recipe. It is important to make this cake a full day before you plan to serve it. The taste definitely improves with age. I ate a piece on the first day, and was not impressed. Yesterday I ate another piece, and was greatly impressed. I think it is an even better recipe than the double chocolate cake recipe, that I also ice with Lindt bittersweet chocolate. It does make a very tall cake. It is also an excellent tasting cake. I took one reviewer's suggestion to heart, and after I buttered my pans, I dusted them with cocoa powder (Ghiradelli). It is important to use parchment paper. Wax paper is not a substitute. Do let the cakes cool before you unmold them. They slip out easily. I iced the cake with Lindt bittersweet chocolate and cream.

