Rating: 3
I made this as a birthday cake for myself:-) YUM! Absolutely delicious. Not too sweet, just right. Read all the comments before you make it. Some of the most helpful ones: this is one BIG cake. I should have halved the recipe. Instead, I made 2 8" layers and 18 cupcakes. I froze one layer and all the cupcakes for later. Make sure you start the eggs and sour cream in your largest mixing bowl, as that is the bowl that will end up with all the batter in it. My 4 1/2 qt. Kitchen-Aid was full to the brim. The butter-parchment paper-butter, and the correct cooling times seem to be key to getting the cake out of the pan. One of the reviewers recommended beating the frosting to make it fluffier, which seemed like a good idea to me. I think it worked well. However, if you are going to use it as a ganache, don't refrigerate it: just let it cool and it thickened nicely. This really is an incredibly good cake.

